parameters.pythonCode:
from datetime import datetime, timezone, timedelta

raw_data = _input.first().json["chart"]["result"][0]

# General Data
long_name = raw_data.meta.longName
short_name = raw_data.meta.shortName
currency = raw_data.meta.currency
symbol = raw_data.meta.symbol
exchange_name = raw_data.meta.exchangeName
full_exchange_name = raw_data.meta.fullExchangeName
instrument_type = raw_data.meta.instrumentType
exchange_timezone_name = raw_data.meta.exchangeTimezoneName

# Dates
dates = raw_data["timestamp"]

# Prices
quote = raw_data["indicators"]["quote"][0]
adjclose = raw_data["indicators"]["adjclose"][0]["adjclose"]

close = quote["close"]
open_ = quote["open"]
low = quote["low"]
high = quote["high"]
volume = quote["volume"]

# Convert timestamp example to IST
IST = timezone(timedelta(hours=5, minutes=30))
records_count = len(dates)

data_list = []
for i in range(records_count):
  dt_utc = datetime.fromtimestamp(dates[i], tz=timezone.utc)
  dt_ist = dt_utc.astimezone(IST)
  entry = {
    "long_name":long_name,
    "short_name":short_name,
    "currency":currency,
    "symbol":symbol,
    "exchange_name":exchange_name,
    "full_exchange_name":full_exchange_name,
    "instrument_type":instrument_type,
    "exchange_timezone_name":exchange_timezone_name,
    "date":dt_ist.isoformat(),
    "close":close[i],
    "open":open_[i],
    "low":low[i],
    "high":high[i],
    "volume":volume[i]
  }
  data_list.append(entry)
  
return {
  "data": data_list
}
